name: URL
description: Represents a uniform resource locator (URL) and provides access to parts of the URL. Enables access to the Salesforce instance URL.

getauthority().name: getAuthority
getauthority().description: Returns the authority portion of the current URL.

getcurrentrequesturl().name: getCurrentRequestUrl
getcurrentrequesturl().description: Returns the URL of an entire request on a Salesforce instance.

getdefaultport().name: getDefaultPort
getdefaultport().description: Returns the default port number of the protocol associated with the current URL.

getfile().name: getFile
getfile().description: Returns the file name of the current URL.

getfilefieldurl(string,string).name: getFileFieldURL
getfilefieldurl(string,string).signature: public static String getFileFieldURL(String entityId, String fieldName)
getfilefieldurl(string,string).overrideSignature: public static override String getFileFieldURL(String entityId, String fieldName)
getfilefieldurl(string,string).description: Returns the download URL for a file attachment.

fieldname.name: fieldName
fieldname.description: Specifies the ID of the entity that holds the file data. Specifies the API name of a file field component, such as AttachmentBody.

gethost().name: getHost
gethost().description: Returns the host name of the current URL.

getorgdomainurl().name: getOrgDomainUrl
getorgdomainurl().description: Returns the canonical URL for your org. For example, https://yourDomain.my.salesforce.com or, for orgs without My Domain enabled, https://yourInstance.salesforce.com.

getpath().name: getPath
getpath().description: Returns the path portion of the current URL.

getport().name: getPort
getport().description: Returns the port of the current URL.

getprotocol().name: getProtocol
getprotocol().description: Returns the protocol name of the current URL, such as, https.

getquery().name: getQuery
getquery().description: Returns the query portion of the current URL.

getref().name: getRef
getref().description: Returns the anchor of the current URL.

getsalesforcebaseurl().name: getSalesforceBaseUrl
getsalesforcebaseurl().description: Returns the URL of the Salesforce instance.

getuserinfo().name: getUserInfo
getuserinfo().description: Gets the UserInfo portion of the current URL.

samefile(system.url).name: sameFile
samefile(system.url).description: Compares the current URL with the specified URL object, excluding the fragment component.

toexternalform().name: toExternalForm
toexternalform().description: Returns a string representation of the current URL.

url(string).name: Url
url(string).description: Creates a new instance of the URL class using the specified string representation of the URL.

spec.name: spec
spec.description: The string to parse as a URL.

url(url,string).name: Url
url(url,string).overrideSignature: public override Url(Url context, String spec)
url(url,string).description: Creates a new instance of the URL class by parsing the specified spec within the specified context.

spec.name: spec
spec.description: The context in which to parse the specification. The string to parse as a URL.

url(string,string,string).name: Url
url(string,string,string).signature: public Url(String protocol, String host, String file)
url(string,string,string).overrideSignature: public override Url(String protocol, String host, String file)
url(string,string,string).description: Creates a new instance of the URL class using the specified protocol, host, and  file on the host. The default port for the specified protocol is used.

file.name: file
file.description: The protocol name for this URL. The host name for this URL. The file name for this URL.

url(string,string,integer,string).name: Url
url(string,string,integer,string).signature: public Url(String protocol, String host, Integer port, String file)
url(string,string,integer,string).overrideSignature: public override Url(String protocol, String host, Integer port, String file)
url(string,string,integer,string).description: Creates a new instance of the URL class using the specified protocol, host, port, and file on the host.

file.name: file
file.description: The protocol name for this URL. The host name for this URL. The port number for this URL. The file name for this URL.
